params._checkpointManager: Checkpoint manager contract for verifying L2 to L1 data (RootChainManagerProxy).
params._l1MessageRelayer: L1 message relayer bridging contract address (fxRoot).
params._l1TokenRelayer: L1 token relayer bridging contract address (RootChainManagerProxy).
params._predicate: ERC20 predicate contract to lock tokens on L1 before sending to L2.

getBridgingDecimals().details: Gets the maximum number of token decimals able to be transferred across the bridge.

receiveMessage(bytes).details: This function verifies if the transaction actually happened on child chain

params.inputData: RLP encoded data of the reference tx containing following list of fields  0 - headerNumber - Checkpoint header block number containing the reference tx  1 - blockProof - Proof that the block header (in the child chain) is a leaf in the submitted merkle root  2 - blockNumber - Block number containing the reference tx on child chain  3 - blockTime - Reference tx block time  4 - txRoot - Transactions root of block  5 - receiptRoot - Receipts root of block  6 - receipt - Receipt of the reference transaction  7 - receiptProof - Merkle proof of the reference receipt  8 - branchMask - 32 bits denoting the path of receipt in merkle tree  9 - receiptLogIndex - Log Index to read from the receipt

params.bridgePayload: Bridge payload necessary (if required) for a specific bridge relayer.
params.transferAmount: Actual OLAS amount to be transferred.

sendMessageBatch(address[],uint256[],byt.details: Sends a batch message to the L2 side via a corresponding bridge.

params.bridgePayload: Bridge payload necessary (if required) for a specific bridge relayer.
params.transferAmount: Actual total OLAS amount across all the targets to be transferred.

updateHashMaintenance(bytes32).details: Updated the batch hash of a failed message, if applicable.
